description:
Four stars:

1.  Great space; you can actually hear your dinner companions as opposed to dining experiences at Town Hall, Salt House, etc. (love them dearly though); 
2.  Yummy food.  Everything that came out of the kitchen was tasty.  My flat iron steak was overcooked the first time, but they were gracious about firing up again and doing it right; 
3.  Nice wines at good prices;
4.  Full bar caters to local companies, which is great, but was still able to make my friend a B&B;
5.  Easy parking.  W00t!;
6.  Our server, Kiiana--what can I say, she just rocks.

I'm a fan and will definitely be back.
